{
  "stem": "13315.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Dachau, when I was there, you didn't have any eastern Jews, so I would have to just fantasize.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later on, actually, especially when they went into Poland, some people were in those camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was mainly eastern Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For Dachau, and for another few camps there. .",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Also the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was mainly-- look, we, in the camp in Dachau, we had to set up facilities for 30,000 Sudeten Germans-- not Jews-- who were arrested because they were not for Hitler.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they wanted to make space for them there, when we would be out-- 30,000.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From then on, I just wanted to get out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then Father finally got the ticket for me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From then on, I had to get ready, pack whatever I was permitted to take with me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I had to go through customs inspection.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had to get a supplement to the passport, because it was outside of Europe.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You see, the passport normally was for European travel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then you needed from the-- what they called it [NON-ENGLISH], that means a place where you wander to, see?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There, you had a confirmation for-- an OK from them in the passport that you could go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the passport had a big J in it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I didn't have yet the Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in Manila, when my passport was about to expire when I wanted to go to the United States-- so I asked-- I thought the best way to-- is find out first.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I went to the American High Commissioner, who was very nice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I told him the passport is about to expire, and when I go to the States and Europe, what we-- what-- what should I do?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, you go to the German embassy there-- consulate.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
